2021, c. 27, s. 87.

280.21. An inspector may send any person the recommendations he considers appropriate.
In the event of a possible failure by a contractor referred to in section 1 of the Act respecting contracting by public bodies (chapter C-65.1) to comply with a contract rule, the inspector shall send his inspection report to the contract rules compliance monitor designated by the Commission.


2021, c. 27, s. 87.

